<h3>Set up Port Forwarding Rule</h3>

<div class="container span7">
<legend>Step 1:</legend>&nbsp;&nbsp;Click on 'Services' tab on the menu bar
</div>

<div class="container span7">
<legend>Step 2:</legend>&nbsp;&nbsp;Select 'Port Forwarding' tab
</div>


<div class="container span7">
<legend>Step 3:</legend>&nbsp;&nbsp;Click "Add new port Mapping" button to create a new rule. You can either create a new rule from scratch, or select an existing rule from the drop down list. 
</div>


<div class="container span7">
<legend>Step 4:</legend>&nbsp;&nbsp;In the new added row, fill in the Name, Protocol , WAN Port, LAN Port, Destination. Click + icon to add the new rule to the device.  
</div>

<div class="container span7">
<legend>Step 5:</legend>&nbsp;&nbsp;You can also click on pencil icon to modify or the red cross icon to delete an exist rule
</div>
